award_winners_and_nominees.title: Award Winners & Nominees
award_winners_and_nominees.description: See the acclaimed movies and shows that earned gold statuettes... or were honored just to be nominated.

300451.title: It's A Mad, Mad, Mad, Mad World
300451.description: A multitude of people have been given a clue by a dying man as to the location of $350,000 in stolen bank money that he has buried and set out separately in a mad race to get to it first.

300465.title: Rob Roy
300465.description: In eighteenth century Scotland, a cattle farmer, who cannot repay his debt to the aristocratic Marquis of Montrose, fights for his integrity.

301943.title: The Scalp Hunters
301943.description: A lively and ribald western about a frontier-wise fur trapper who loses his pelts to a band of Kiowas in exchange for a slave he doesn't want.

302148.title: The Children's Hour
302148.description: In this provocatively daring film, an attention-seeking schoolgirl vengefully spreads rumors that two of her teachers are lesbian lovers.

302695.title: Last Tango In Paris
302695.description: A man, torn apart by his wife's suicide, attempts to bury his grief in a sudden, purely carnal relationship with an alluring, young stranger.

302711.title: The Madness Of King George
302711.description: In late 18th century England, the benevolent King George III takes ill, showing signs of madness, opening the door to be usurped by his worthless son.

303080.title: Henry V
303080.description: In the midst of the Hundred Years War, a young and uncertain King Henry V defeats the French but learns that victory takes its toll in bloodshed.

303190.title: The Usual Suspects
303190.description: The lone survivor of a heist-gone-wrong tells the feds how it all went down as they search for the enigmatic crime lord behind the disaster.

304802.title: The Greatest Story Ever Told
304802.description: With an all-star cast, the life and teachings of Jesus Christ of Nazareth are retold on a grand scale in this inspiring, larger-than-life film.

304804.title: Holiday Heart
304804.description: In this heartwarming story, a drag queen takes in a mother and daughter and helps raise the girl while her mother battles with drug addiction.

304806.title: Inherit The Wind
304806.description: Spencer Tracy and Frederic March go head-to-head as opposing attorneys in this blistering courtroom drama about the famed "Scopes Monkey Trial" where a Tennessee teacher must defend himself for teaching Darwinism.

304810.title: Thunderbolt and Lightfoot
304810.description: While fleeing from a theft, a drifter meets a legendary criminal who's also on the run. The duo reunite with their old partners to plan a bank heist.

305031.title: Witness For The Prosecution
305031.description: A courtroom drama about a young man on trial for a wealthy widow's murder after he suspiciously profits from her will.

305870.title: Lilies of the Field
305870.description: A warm, sensitive handyman, stranded in an Arizona desert town, builds a chapel for a lively group of nuns.

306940.title: The Pink Panther Strikes Again
306940.description: After escaping from an insane asylum, the hilariously crazy Chief Inspector Dreyfus (Herbert Lom) sends 26 assassins on the trail of hapless Inspector Closeau (Peter Sellers).

310136.title: Hotel Rwanda
310136.description: The true story of a brave hotel manager who risked his and his family’s lives to harbor over 1,000 refugees during the 1994 Rwandan genocide.

310154.title: 12 Angry Men
310154.description: A twelve-person jury becomes increasingly tense with arguments continuing into the night as one juror must convince the other eleven he is right.

312187.title: Midnight Cowboy
312187.description: This Academy Award-winning Best Picture features Dustin Hoffman and Jon Voight in standout roles as a con man and a Texas hustler trying to survive on the tough streets of New York.

312417.title: Hoosiers
312417.description: A man gets a last chance at redemption by coaching a small-town Indiana high-school basketball team and bring his team to the 1951 state championship.

312421.title: Marty
312421.description: Ernest Borgnine stars as Marty, a lonely Bronx butcher who gives up on love -- until he meets an equally lonely school teacher in this charming story.

316463.title: Rabbit Hole
316463.description: A married couple grieves the loss of their young son. Director John Cameron Mitchell brings a restrained hand to this moving film.

334153.title: Exodus
334153.description: Following WWII, a rebel soldier helps 600 Holocaust survivors escape from British internment camps to get to Palestine, where a new nation is born.

356528.title: Bowling for Columbine
356528.description: This documentary examines gun violence in the U.S. in relation to other countries, including the specific events that led to the Columbine massacre.

356529.title: A Fish Called Wanda
356529.description: After pulling off a diamond heist, the motley crew of culprits dupe one another repeatedly in hopes of pocketing the loot, in this black comedy.

358575.title: Mississippi Burning
358575.description: Based on the true story, two FBI agents investigate the disappearance of three Mississippi civil rights activists in 1964.

389503.title: Robocop
389503.description: A cop who died in the line of duty is transformed into a chrome-plated cyborg policeman with an indestructible new body and a thirst for revenge.

399691.title: Requiem for a Dream
399691.description: The lives of four people intertwine in this gut-wrenching, hypnotic tale of addiction and the devastation it has on their lives and those around them.

441470.title: Super Size Me
441470.description: Documentarian Morgan Spurlock explores the consequences on his health of a one-month diet consisting solely of items from the McDonald's menu.

448257.title: Amores Perros
448257.description: A horrific car accident connects the lives of three strangers: a lovesick dog fighter, an injured supermodel and a hitman running from his past.

449335.title: Pawn Shop Chronicles
449335.description: A missing wedding ring is the trigger for  a madcap, wild-goose chase involving meth addicts, skinheads, and an Elvis impersonator.

457783.title: The Crime of Padre Amaro
457783.description: A newly-ordained Catholic priest arrives in a Mexican village, where corruption, temptation, and sexual passion threaten his calling and salvation.

462800.title: Enron: the Smartest Guys in the Room
462800.description: The rise and fall of Enron is the focus as executives got rich pretending the company was more profitable while lower-level employees lost everything.

463715.title: On Golden Pond
463715.description: At Golden Pond, a couple agree to care of Billy, the son of their daughter Chelsea's new boyfriend, and a most unexpected relationship blooms.

465429.title: Seal Team Six: The Raid on Osama Bin Laden
465429.description: A portrayal of the historic mission of an elite military unit, who entered Pakistan to take down the world’s most wanted terrorist, Osama bin Laden.

465430.title: Gimme Shelter
465430.description: The true story of a pregnant teen runaway traces her journey from an abusive home to the mean streets, and finally, to a place that offers hope.

466023.title: Running Scared
466023.description: Two policemen in wintry Chicago put off their tropical retirement plans when their nemesis, a ruthless drug dealer and murderer, evades custody.

475177.title: All Things Fair
475177.description: A forbidden relationship between a teen student and his adult, female teacher in World War II-era Sweden has consequences neither of them expect.

479898.title: An American Crime
479898.description: A frustrated mother descends into cruelty after taking in two girls, imprisoning and torturing one of them in her basement. Based on a true story.

480284.title: Bernie
480284.description: When a lovable mortician in a Texas town gets involved with a rich, nasty widow, she tightens her grip and steers him on a course toward a murder rap.

497272.title: Hands of Stone
497272.description: Legendary boxer Roberto Duran and his renowned trainer change each other’s lives, as they battle Sugar Ray Leonard for the WBC welterweight crown.

499716.title: Stagecoach
499716.description: Western classic that transcends the genre as a stagecoach carrying nine passengers through frontier wilderness faces an impending Apache attack.

506145.title: The Wailing
506145.description: A policeman races against time to save his daughter from a mysterious sickness spreading through a small village.

506707.title: Animal Farm
506707.description: George Orwell’s classic tale of a revolution among farm animals teaches a lesson on the cost of keeping social order with an uneven power balance.

507479.title: Gold
507479.description: A prospector out to strike gold gets a rare chance at his goal when he goes on an incredible trip to the Indonesian jungle with a gung-ho geologist.

512252.title: We Need to Talk About Kevin
512252.description: In this suspenseful and gripping psychological thriller, a mother contends for years with the increasing malevolence of her first-born child, Kevin.

514356.title: Red River (Colorized)
514356.description: Colorized version of the Western classic about a desperate cattle drive over the famed Chisholm Trail as male rivals juggle revenge and determination.

526872.title: The Librarian: Curse of the Judas Chalice
526872.description: A mild-mannered scholar scours mystical New Orleans to find an ancient silver cup, rumored to have the power to bring a Romanian vampire back to life.

526874.title: The Librarian: Return to King Solomon's Mines
526874.description: A lovable antiquities scholar and a brainy archaeologist hunt for a legendary holy book, but must elude a sinister general and a scheming uncle.

531445.title: Threads
531445.description: After a young English couple are separated by a nuclear attack, they must fight for their lives in a frightening post-apocalyptic world.

537388.title: David
537388.description: The true story of David Rothenberg, a young boy whose mentally disturbed father set him on fire, traces his trauma and hard path to recovery.

539677.title: Lion
539677.description: A young man makes an emotional journey to reconnect with his birth family in India after being tragically separated from them years earlier.

540237.title: The Lover
540237.description: The forbidden and risky romance between a French teenager and a wealthy, older Chinese man in 1929 French Indochina has the power to ruin their lives.

543161.title: Apocalypto
543161.description: A Mayan warrior braves the treacherous jungle to fight off attacking members of an opposing tribe in order to save his family.

544424.title: Kilo Two Bravo
544424.description: In war-torn Afghanistan, British soldiers risk life and limb on a mission to rescue fellow servicemen from a dried-out river rigged with explosives.

544522.title: The Pride of the Yankees
544522.description: From joining the New York Yankees to wedding his sweetheart to the brutal disease that would end his life, this is the story of a baseball legend.

545172.title: Broken Arrow
545172.description: Western drama about a man trying to broker peace, with dramatic consequences, between settlers and Apaches in a time of tribal mistrust.

545196.title: Stalag 17
545196.description: When two escaping American World War II prisoners are killed, the German P.O.W. camp barracks black marketeer is suspected of being an informer.

545825.title: Guys and Dolls
545825.description: In this musical comedy, a slick gambler with a girlfriend and a high-roller debt makes a bet with his friend to get a chilly missionary on a date.

549640.title: Cartel Land
549640.description: A stark look at two Mexican drug cartel hot-spots and the two separate vigilante groups who've taken justice to eradicate crime into their own hands.

550824.title: The Hunger Games
550824.description: In a dystopian future, 16-year-old Katniss volunteers to take her younger sister’s place in a battle where children must fight to stay alive.

550826.title: The Hunger Games: Catching Fire
550826.description: As Katniss and Peeta embark on their victory tour, President Snow plans an even deadlier new Hunger Games, which threatens the future of Panem.

550828.title: The Hunger Games: Mockingjay Part 2
550828.description: The celebrated movie series reaches its epic climax, as the brave Katniss fights to liberate Panem's citizens in a final showdown with President Snow.

550864.title: The Passion of the Christ
550864.description: The brutal portrayal of the final hours in the life of Jesus, as he is betrayed by Judas, condemned to death, tortured, and yet performs one last act of grace.

551255.title: The Hunger Games: Mockingjay Part 1
551255.description: The franchise phenomenon continues, as Katniss, having survived The Hunger Games, rises with District 13 to battle the oppressive President Snow.

552975.title: Ozzy
552975.description: When his family goes on vacation, a beloved dog is dropped off at a fancy kennel, which turns out to be a canine prison that he must escape.

564235.title: A Woman Scorned: The Betty Broderick Story
564235.description: Left by her renowned lawyer husband for his secretary, a scorned San Diego socialite and soccer mom gets the ultimate revenge. Based on a true story.

566803.title: A Man Called Ove
566803.description: When a boisterous Persian family, including a pregnant woman, moves next door to the neighborhood’s grumpy old man, unexpected love and kinship bloom.

577680.title: How to Murder Your Wife
577680.description: A rich bachelor finds his swinging lifestyle ruined when he awakens one morning having married the gorgeous lady who popped out of a cake.

579647.title: Fahrenheit 9/11
579647.description: The definitive exposé revealing how and why the Bush Administration manufactured evidence to invade war in Iraq following the 2001 terrorist attacks.

580530.title: Detroit
580530.description: This relevant, fact-based story, set in 1967’s Detroit riots, tracks a group of rogue cops, who respond to a call with vengeance instead of justice.

581879.title: Miss Potter
581879.description: In Victorian England, an aspiring female writer overcomes a difficult home life and a patriarchal society to become a best-selling children’s author.

597657.title: Notorious
597657.description: A woman is asked to spy on a group of Nazi friends in South America. How far will she have to go to ingratiate herself with them?

599629.title: Eyes Wide Shut
599629.description: Tom Cruise and Nicole Kidman star as a married couple entangled in an intricate web of jealousy and sexual obsession in Stanley Kubrick's final cinematic offering.  At a Christmas party hosted by wealthy, unconventional Victor Ziegler (Sydney Pollack), provocative advances and innocent flirtations arouse suspicion as high-society physician Dr. William Harford (Cruise) and his sexy wife, Alice (Kidman) watch each other from a distance. Alone later, this seemingly perfect couple confront their intimate sexual fantasies--which don't include each other.  Caught between reality and illusion, jealousy and obsession, William struggles with his inner urges. Will he act on his erotic fantasies or keep them hidden deep inside? Sometimes a man can see more clearly with his Eyes Wide Shut.

602919.title: Sudden Fear
602919.description: A successful playwright comes to discover the masked motives of her new struggling actor husband for marrying her — and love isn’t one of them.

607451.title: E.T. The Extra-Terrestrial
607451.description: A boy forms a special bond with a sweet and gifted alien from another planet. He tries to keep it a secret, but he needs help to keep the visitor safe.

610572.title: Goodfellas
610572.description: Based on a true story, a young man rises up the ranks of a mob family over several years, dabbling in drugs, heists and murders along the way.

617447.title: Pretty Woman
617447.description: Julia Roberts stars as a witty prostitute who charms a serious businessman, as the two unlikely lovers fall for each other over the course of a week.

622846.title: Australia
622846.description: With the threat of war looming, a landowner in Australia fights to keep her cattle and her land with the help of a seasoned ranch hand.

628023.title: The Best Little Whorehouse in Texas
628023.description: This rousing musical portrays a sheriff and a madam, who band together to save the infamous Texas Chicken Ranch from a big-city TV crusader.

628970.title: Hellboy II: The Golden Army
628970.description: Hellboy and his crew of paranormal outcasts face off with forces of darkness in this imaginative adventure from visionary director Guillermo del Toro.

629889.title: Charley Varrick
629889.description: Walter Matthau plays a petty thief who knocks off a mob bank and soon finds that both the police and a hit man are chasing after him.

637929.title: Carlito's Way
637929.description: In 1975 NYC, a rehabilitated ex-con drug dealer determined to stay clean is tempted back into the life by an array of lowlifes and former associates.

639974.title: To Wong Foo, Thanks for Everything! Julie Newmar
639974.description: John Leguizamo, Wesley Snipes, and Patrick Swayze are triple threats in this road trip romp about three drag queens who get stranded in a small town.

640031.title: Blackfish
640031.description: Award-winning documentary about the ethics of taking killer whales captive, especially after a loving trainer’s public death in a Sea World enclosure.

641581.title: Somewhere in Time
641581.description: A playwright visiting a hotel falls in love with an actress pictured in a 1912 photo and uses self-hypnosis to go 68 years back in time to meet her.

642254.title: The Girl with All the Gifts
642254.description: In a bleak future, mankind has succumbed to a fungus that turns everyone into flesh-eating monsters, until an immune child is discovered.

643081.title: West Side Story
643081.description: This electrifying musical, winner of ten Academy Awards, including Best Picture, reimagines “Romeo and Juliet,” set during gang warfare in 1950s NYC.

643528.title: Beaches
643528.description: A lifelong friendship between two women, one a demure, privileged socialite, the other a bold, struggling singer, takes unexpected twists and turns.

646733.title: Escape From Sobibor
646733.description: In 1943, a Polish Jew, a Russian officer, and a seamstress lead the war’s most successful prisoner escape from a Nazi death camp in eastern Poland.

651120.title: The Tourist
651120.description: An American tourist visiting Italy to mend a broken heart is seduced by a beautiful woman, who ensnares him in an international criminal plot.

652002.title: Western
652002.description: Drug cartel violence and border politics destroy a previously friendly atmosphere between Eagle Pass, Texas, and Piedras Negras, Mexico.

652270.title: The Goonies
652270.description: A pair of brothers hope to save their house by following a treasure map and taking their friends along on a subterranean sea adventure.

658082.title: To Die For
658082.description: Suzanne is dead set on being a famous TV reporter. When her husband asks her to give up her dream, she plots against him with a love-struck teenager.

663544.title: Country Strong
663544.description: A fallen country star strives to resurrect her career with help from her songwriter husband and an emerging artist with a rapidly growing fan base.

663814.title: The Sisters Brothers
663814.description: Brothers and assassins Eli and Charlie Sisters pursue a prospector across the American Northwest in this witty reimagining of the cinematic Western.

665462.title: Apollo 13
665462.description: A routine space flight becomes a desperate battle of survival in this breathtaking and true-story of adventure, courage, and faith.

667137.title: 12 Angry Men
667137.description: A fair-minded juror exposes holes in the prosecution's case to create a reasonable doubt and cast light on the biases that often pollute the system.

667422.title: Pacific Rim
667422.description: With alien invaders rising from the sea, a washed-up former pilot and an untested trainee use massive robots to combat the apocalyptic threat.

671658.title: Alice in Wonderland
671658.description: When a young girl falls asleep in a meadow, she dreams of entering a magical fantasy land filled with strange adventures and magical creatures.

672503.title: Death on the Nile
672503.description: While detective Hercule Poirot is enjoying some R&R on a luxurious cruise down the Nile River, a newlywed heiress is found murdered on board.

676660.title: The Babadook
676660.description: A mother struggles to protect her son from an evil supernatural entity that has escaped the pages of a children's book and is lurking in their home.

676665.title: The Death of Stalin
676665.description: Follows the wild scramble for power inside the Council of Ministers upon the sudden illness and death of Soviet dictator Joseph Stalin in 1953.

676725.title: Boyhood
676725.description: Richard Linklater's acclaimed hit, filmed over twelve years with the same cast, is a groundbreaking celebration of life, growing up, and parenting.

676860.title: Bone Tomahawk
676860.description: When a group of individuals kidnaps settlers from a small town, an unlikely team of gunslingers, led by Sheriff Hunt, sets out to bring them home.

681750.title: Touching the Void
681750.description: An incredible account of tragedy and friendship, this film follows two men's thrilling and disastrous climb of the treacherous Siula Grande in Peru.

681752.title: The Snowtown Murders
681752.description: After a charismatic serial murderer befriends a troubled teen, he slowly seduces him into a darkly violent and unforgiving new world.

684126.title: The Stanford Prison Experiment
684126.description: Based on the infamous true story, two dozen students role play as prisoners and guards in a terrifying experiment that shocked the world.

684127.title: Sleeping Beauty
684127.description: A haunting portrait of a shy co-ed who allows a coin toss to spark her first impromptu sexual encounter and immerse her in a dark new world.

684138.title: The House That Jack Built
684138.description: An architect-turned-serial killer who views murder as art recounts his "life's work" in this audacious film from visionary Lars von Trier.

684149.title: Camp X-Ray
684149.description: A young Guantanamo prison guard forms an unlikely relationship with a longtime inmate in this riveting psychological drama.

689650.title: The Pink Panther
689650.description: The bumbling Inspector Jacques Clouseau tries to catch an infamous jewel thief before he can steal a priceless diamond from a princess.

689652.title: In the Heat of the Night
689652.description: While traveling in the deep south, a black Philadelphian homicide detective becomes embroiled in a murder investigation.

690311.title: The Reader
690311.description: In post-WWII Germany, a law student finds the older woman with whom he had an affair eight years ago, among Nazi prison guards being tried for murder.

692118.title: Holy Hell
692118.description: This documentary looks at Buddhafield, a West Hollywood cult, through the eyes of a then young idealist who formed a part of it for twenty years.

694011.title: Vice
694011.description: This acclaimed biopic explores how Dick Cheney quietly wielded immense power as George W. Bush's Vice President, reshaping the U.S. and the globe.

698087.title: Zulu
698087.description: Counting only 100 among their ranks, outnumbered British soldiers do battle with 4,000 Zulu warriors at the 1879 Battle of Rorke's Drift.

700349.title: The Final Solution
700349.description: With archival footage from 16 countries, this Oscar-nominated film presents important facts about the Nazis' persecution against Jews during WWII.

703907.title: Ride to Freedom: The Rosa Parks Story
703907.description: Rosa Parks recalls events leading to her peaceful defiance against racial bus segregation and inspiring the 1955 Montgomery Bus Boycott.

707103.title: Blazing Saddles
707103.description: A corrupt governor will grant a reprieve to a convict under one condition: the condemned man agrees to serve as sheriff of a small Western town.

712894.title: The Help
712894.description: In 1960s Mississippi, a Southern girl turns her small town on its ear when she interviews African-American maids who have worked for white families.

714943.title: Don Juan DeMarco
714943.description: After losing his one true love and attempting suicide, a man who believes he’s the mythical Don Juan is placed in the care of a world-weary therapist.

714948.title: Michael Collins
714948.description: One of Ireland's most controversial patriots and revolutionary heroes leads his countrymen in the early 20th century in their fight for independence.

716409.title: With Honors
716409.description: A homeless man holds a stuffy Ivy League student's misplaced graduate thesis hostage in return for room and board - one page for every day.

720943.title: Burlesque
720943.description: A small-town singer moves to the city for a chance at fame when she finds a glamorous nightclub packed with dancers and an owner in need of a star.

723250.title: Bend It Like Beckham
723250.description: Despite the wishes of their traditional families, two young women from different walks of life aim for a career in professional soccer.

723254.title: Master and Commander: The Far Side of the World
723254.description: A distinguished young captain of the British Navy leads his crew on a mission to take a French vessel with a reputation for sinking British ships.

723505.title: The Ladykillers
723505.description: An eccentric Southern professor and his crew pose as a band in order to rob a casino, all under the nose of his unsuspecting landlord.

723627.title: Antichrist
723627.description: A controversial, sexually provocative drama about a broken couple's twisted and erotic journey in the wake of their infant son’s guilt-fueling death.

724347.title: The Best Man
724347.description: A Chicago author forces his old friend group to confront secrets from the past when he arrives in town for his best friend’s wedding with a new book.

724377.title: Downfall
724377.description: Traudl Junge, the final secretary for Adolf Hitler, tells of the Nazi dictator's final days in his Berlin bunker at the end of World War II.

724420.title: The Way Back
724420.description: A band of convicts stages an escape from a World War II Siberian gulag and embarks on a 4,000-mile journey on foot across five countries to freedom.

724713.title: Blue Is the Warmest Color
724713.description: A young French student finds love and affection for the first time with a lover when she begins a passionate relationship with a free-spirited woman.

725388.title: House of Pleasures
725388.description: A 16-year-old girl is thrust into indentured servitude as she begins life as a sex worker inside the lavish Apollonide bordello in early-1900’s Paris.

100000001.title: Kubo and the Two Strings
100000001.description: After accidentally summoning an evil spirit, Kubo must recover his fallen samurai father’s mystical weaponry and discover his own magical powers.

100000105.title: The Housemaid
100000105.description: In this suspenseful, erotic thriller, a scandalous affair between a beautiful young maid and her wealthy employer has shocking consequences.

100000171.title: Bohemian Rhapsody
100000171.description: Celebrates the rock band Queen, their music and their extraordinary frontman in the years leading up to their appearance at 1985's Live Aid concert.

100000218.title: The Secret in Their Eyes
100000218.description: A recently retired criminal court investigator writes a novel based on a twenty-five-year-old unresolved rape and murder case, which still haunts him.

100000302.title: Real Steel
100000302.description: In a near future where human boxers have been replaced by robots, a struggling ex-boxer and his estranged son reunite while training a robot fighter.

100000784.title: Ghostbusters
100000784.description: A trio of failed university parapsychologists cash in on an uptick in New Yorkers’ paranormal complaints by setting up a ghost extermination service.

100000844.title: Exam
100000844.description: When eight candidates enter a windowless room to compete for a job at a mysterious and powerful company, the stakes soon become life or death.

100001274.title: A Bridge Too Far
100001274.description: In the midst of WWII, the Allies devise an ill-fated mission to push through German lines in the Netherlands, but a key bridge stands in the way.

100001288.title: Meteor
100001288.description: An American scientist learns that a huge meteor is hurtling towards Earth, and the only way to stop it is to share nuclear secrets with the USSR.

100001338.title: The Survivalist
100001338.description: After a deadly apocalypse, two hungry women come upon a survivalist who grows his own vegetables, making a dangerous bargain in exchange for food.

100001489.title: Run the Wild Fields
100001489.description: On a North Carolina farm, a woman and her daughter take in a mysterious drifter while the woman's husband is missing in action during WWII.

100001834.title: Mighty Joe Young
100001834.description: A 15-foot gorilla is removed from his habitat in Africa and brought to California where he falls victim to poachers, promoters and conservationists.

100001962.title: Echoes in the Darkness
100001962.description: In this chilling true story, a seven-year investigation into the murder of a teacher and her children leads to the discovery of a shocking conspiracy.

100002073.title: Mr. Peabody & Sherman
100002073.description: A canine inventor and his human son travel through time to witness the most important events in history, but a rift in time endangers the future.

100002087.title: King Kong
100002087.description: A devious producer leads his crew to an ominous island full of deadly creatures, where a giant ape becomes captivated by the film’s leading lady.

100002112.title: Kill Bill: Vol. 1
100002112.description: After waking up from a four-year coma, a former assassin seeks revenge on the team of killers that betrayed her—and that she was once a part of.

100002113.title: Jackie Brown
100002113.description: Female flight attendant Jackie Brown becomes a key figure in a plot between the federal authorities and her street-tough arms dealer boss.

100002156.title: Men in Black
100002156.description: Tasked with policing extraterrestrial activities on Earth, two agents join forces to track down a dangerous alien intent upon galactic destruction.

100002159.title: Kill Bill: Vol. 2
100002159.description: The Bride continues her quest for revenge, fighting her way through a host of assassins in pursuit of a final showdown with the man who betrayed her.

100002270.title: Judas and the Black Messiah
100002270.description: FBI informant William O’Neal infiltrates the Illinois Black Panther Party and is tasked with keeping tabs on their charismatic leader, Fred Hampton.

100002272.title: In the Heights
100002272.description: The streets are made of music and little dreams become big in Washington Heights, where magnetic bodega owner Usnavi fantasizes about a better life.

100002324.title: Life of Pi
100002324.description: En route to a new life in Canada, an Indian teen loses his family at sea and is set adrift for 227 days in a lifeboat with a 450-pound Bengal tiger.

100002343.title: Backdraft
100002343.description: Two clashing sibling firefighters with the Chicago Fire Department must set aside their differences to solve a puzzling series of arson attacks.

100002833.title: Minari
100002833.description: A Korean-American family moves to a farm in search of their own American Dream, finding hope and a new home.

100002840.title: The Last Black Man in San Francisco
100002840.description: Jimmie and his best friend Mont try to reclaim the home built by his grandfather, launching them on a poignant odyssey to find a place to call home.

100002844.title: Zola
100002844.description: A Detroit waitress is seduced into a weekend of stripping in Florida in this dazzling saga based on the greatest Twitter story ever told.

100003156.title: Back to the Future
100003156.description: Marty McFly is blasted to 1955 in a time machine created by Doc Brown and finds himself in a time-shattering situation that jeopardizes his future.

100003157.title: Back to the Future Part II
100003157.description: Marty McFly and Doc Brown launch themselves to the year 2015 to fine-tune the future and inadvertently disrupt the spacetime continuum.

0300007844.title: Braceface
0300007844.description: Alicia Silverstone stars as the voice of Sharon Spitz, aka Braceface, whose magical braces help her make the leap from middle school to high school!

0300009901.title: Lovecraft Country
0300009901.description: Atticus Freema joins his friend Letitia and his uncle George to embark on a road trip across 1950's Jim Crow America in search of his missing father.

0300009401.title: Running Wild with Bear Grylls
0300009401.description: Famed survivalist Bear Grylls takes six celebrities into the most remote and wild locations around the world for a 48-hour journey of a lifetime.

0300010215.title: The Secret
0300010215.description: Well-respected dentist Colin Howell and Sunday school teacher Hazel Buchanan meet at their local Baptist church to plot the murders of their partners.

0300010105.title: One Day at a Time
0300010105.description: This situation comedy revolves around a single mother trying to be an understanding parent to her two headstrong teenage daughters.

0300000125.title: Welcome Back, Kotter
0300000125.description: This series follows teacher Gabe Kotter as he returns to his former high school to teach a remedial class of students known as the “Sweathogs.”

0300008096.title: The Dick Van Dyke Show
0300008096.description: Laugh along to one of television's most beloved shows, centering on a TV comedy writer, his charming wife, and goofy office colleagues.

0300010224.title: Scarecrow and Mrs. King
0300010224.description: A single mother in suburban Washington, D.C. discovers she has a talent for espionage work when she meets a dashing undercover agent.

0300000197.title: A Woman of Independent Means
0300000197.description: Follows seven decades of love, loss and courage in the life of a member of Dallas’ high society through her two marriages, three children and beyond.

0300010082.title: Third Watch
0300010082.description: A drama about the brave and dedicated people who serve as paramedics, firefighters, and police on the “third watch,” the 3:00 PM to 11:00 PM shift.

0300008303.title: Gimme a Break!
0300008303.description: A widowed, overworked police captain with three rambunctious daughters matches wits with a feisty housekeeper, who enforces law and order at home.

0300007797.title: Project Runway All Stars
0300007797.description: Fashion designers from past episodes show off their style, as they come back to compete for another chance to be the winner of Project Runway.

0300008457.title: The Jeffersons
0300008457.description: Class, race, neighbors, family, and all kinds of clashes make for classic comedy in this beloved series about a family’s move on up to luxury living.

0300009902.title: Southland
0300009902.description: When a seasoned cop is assigned to train a rookie, his no-nonsense approach makes the young man question if he has what it takes to become an officer.

0300008984.title: Da Vinci’s Demons
0300008984.description: Tortured young genius, artist, and inventor, Leonardo Da Vinci, defies authority and throws himself into the future, changing the fate of humanity.

0300009077.title: The Temptations
0300009077.description: One of Motown's most successful vocal acts was forced to battle prejudice, betrayal, drug abuse and more to become R&B and soul music royalty.

0300009344.title: MasterChef
0300009344.description: Returning contestants vie for the top prize as MasterChef reopens its doors to some of the most memorable cooks in the competition’s history.

0300010244.title: Miami Vice
0300010244.description: From executive producer Michael Mann comes the explosive, groundbreaking detective show that redefined the word "cool” in the mid-1980s.

0300000158.title: Hemlock Grove
0300000158.description: As a once-vibrant and now struggling community’s secrets begin to unravel, Hemlock Grove forces us to ask: What is the true nature of a monster?

0300000081.title: Hell on Wheels
0300000081.description: An epic story of post-Civil War America, focusing on a Confederate soldier who sets out to exact revenge on the Union soldiers who killed his wife.

0300009738.title: Sister, Sister
0300009738.description: Identical twins, separated at birth and adopted by different families, finally meet and try to bring their two very different parents together.

0300008354.title: Airwolf
0300008354.description: A crack test pilot from an elite government intel group flies a supersonic aerial weapon on top secret missions that bypass congressional approval.

0300006342.title: Shameless
0300006342.description: In the Gallagher home, chaos is king, as the unconventional family runs through endless scams, affairs, and petty crimes throughout Manchester.

0300008453.title: Bret Maverick
0300008453.description: James Garner returns to his original role of the slick pro poker player Bret Maverick as he settles into high adventure in the town of Sweetwater.

0300006728.title: Columbo
0300006728.description: This beloved series features the brilliant bumbling detective who despite his easygoing nature, always manages to crack the case.

0300008079.title: The Bernie Mac Show
0300008079.description: Bernie Mac stars as a stand up comic who, alongside his businesswoman wife, must take in his sister's three kids while she's in rehab.

0300008430.title: How the West Was Won
0300008430.description: A Virginia-based family leaves their home to bravely travel across the country and make a new life in the wild, untamed American West.

0300010071.title: Babylon 5
0300010071.description: 2258 CE. The lone space station Babylon 5 stands as the last and best hope for peace between a hundred worlds, alien and human alike.

0300007917.title: Secrets and Lies
0300007917.description: Juliette Lewis stars as a determined and brilliant detective whose latest murder case challenges her and her team with a family’s secrets and lies.

0300000159.title: Hannibal
0300000159.description: An FBI investigator with the ability to empathize with psychopaths is assigned to work with renowned psychiatrist—and secret cannibal—Hannibal Lecter.

0300009559.title: Farscape
0300009559.description: Thrown into a distant part of the universe, an Earth astronaut finds himself part of a fugitive alien starship crew.

0300007796.title: Project Runway
0300007796.description: Models and fashion icons judge the works of clothing designers in this intense reality competition series that showcases up-and-coming artists.

0300000066.title: Lost Civilizations
0300000066.description: Special effects and dramatizations bring to life events and rituals from the Maya, Egyptian, Roman and other ancient cultures and civilizations.

0300007922.title: Rowan & Martin's Laugh-In
0300007922.description: Join comedy duo Dan Rowan and Dick Martin in their classic sketch comedy series, which takes cues from vaudeville and rapid-fire satire.

03320.title: Hell's Kitchen
03320.description: Renowned restauranteur Gordon Ramsay hosts a fierce competition for aspiring chefs, as they vie for a prestigious job at one of his eateries.

0300000120.title: Barney Miller
0300000120.description: This sitcom follows a New York City precinct captain and his diverse band of officers as they handle local troubles in Greenwich Village.

0300010081.title: Nikita
0300010081.description: Betrayed by the secret government agency that made her an assassin, the charming and deadly Nikita makes it her mission to undermine the organization.

0300008044.title: The Inbetweeners
0300008044.description: Four friends in public school enjoy their last years of shenanigans, as they prepare to face the real world in this hilarious series.
